abstract: With four days until the Iowa caucuses, Joe Biden is looking beyond his Democratic rivals and taking square aim at President Donald Trump as the two men campaign within miles of each other on the same day.
snippet: With four days until the Iowa caucuses, Joe Biden is looking beyond his Democratic rivals and taking square aim at President Donald Trump as the two men campaign within miles of each other on the same day.
lead_paragraph: WAUKEE, Iowa — With four days until the Iowa caucuses, Joe Biden is looking beyond his Democratic rivals and taking square aim at President Donald Trump as the two men campaign within miles of each other on the same day.
headline_main: Aiming at Trump, Biden Says a President's Character Matters
headline_print_headline: Aiming at Trump, Biden Says a President's Character Matters

abstract: On Thursday, Mr. Dershowitz said in a tweet that his comment is being mischaracterized.
snippet: On Thursday, Mr. Dershowitz said in a tweet that his comment is being mischaracterized.
lead_paragraph: Democrats are expected to question Alan Dershowitz, one of Mr. Trump’s lawyers, a day after he argued that the president can do whatever he must to get re-elected, because that is in the public’s interest.
headline_main: Democrats plan to question Dershowitz’s expansive powers argument.

abstract: The commerce secretary said the virus, while “very unfortunate,” could prompt companies to reconsider operating inside China.
snippet: The commerce secretary said the virus, while “very unfortunate,” could prompt companies to reconsider operating inside China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Commerce Secretary Wilbur Ross predicted Thursday morning that a deadly virus originating in China would cause companies to reconsider their global supply chains and ultimately “help to accelerate” the return of jobs to the United States.

abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo made the stark statement at a meeting with his British counterpart, where he also talked up the prospect of a U.S. trade deal with Britain.
snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo made the stark statement at a meeting with his British counterpart, where he also talked up the prospect of a U.S. trade deal with Britain.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo declared the Chinese Communist Party “the central threat of our times” on Thursday, even as he sought to talk up the prospects of a United States trade deal with Britain, which rebuffed American pressure to ban a Chinese company from future telecommunications infrastructure.

abstract: Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas will speak in the United Nations Security Council in the next two weeks about the U.S. Middle East peace plan, Palestinian U.N. envoy Riyad Mansour said on Wednesday.

abstract: The White House is considering further restrictions on U.S. airlines flying to and from China in addition to voluntary restrictions that the companies have put into place, President Donald Trump's economic adviser Larry Kudlow said on Wednesday.

headline_main: Restrictions for Airlines Flying to China Under Discussion: White House's Kudlow
